- What was God's original intent for marriage? Genesis 2:18 - God said: man should not be alone, I will make for him a helper. The two shall become one flesh
- God created marriage as a sacred covenant. People read books, see therapists and read blogs about how to have good marriage. They should just read the words of the creator who initated marraiage as a thing. He institutes the first marriage
- The read the words spoken by his son Jesus about rules around divorce
- God has not changed his mind about marriage. Humans have veered away from Gods truth and original design for marriage
- One flesh. Permanent. Two merge into one. Two lives become so intricately intertwined that separation is not possible
- Marriage terminates with death
- Divorce was invented as a way out of honouring a promise
- People are getting divorced for frivolous issues. Jesus is not condemning legitimate divorce on the grounds of sexual immorality, he's clearing up the confusion and being very explicit about divorce
